{"lemma":"طَرِيقَةٍ","slug":"طَرِيقَةٍ","root":"ط.ر.ق","root_slug":"ط-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طَرِيقَة","root":"طرق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26664","n26668"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manner, mode, means"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way, path, method, procedure, course of action"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"system"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creed, faith, religion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"religious brotherhood, dervish order"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"طَرِيق (ṭarīq, “road”) + ـَة (-a)"},"ipa":["/tˤa.riː.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26664","headword_ar":"طَرِيقَةٌ","root":"Trq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, rule, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, TA, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyrapN","text_ar":"سِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masolakN","text_ar":"مَسْلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,) of a man, (S, TA,) whether it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disapproved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is metaphorically used in this sense: (Er-Rághib, TA:) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", often"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to the doctrines and practices of religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and often used in post-classical times as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rule"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a religious order or sect:] and meaning also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a manner of being; a state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", O, K;) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAla fulaAnN EalaY TariyqapK waAHidapK","text_ar":"مَا زَالَ فُلَانٌ عَلَى طَرِيقَةٍ وَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one ceased not to be in one state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) and it is applied to such as is good and to such as is evil. (O.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EalaY","text_ar":"هُوَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tariyqatihi","text_ar":"طَرِيقَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is following his own way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiy~apN","text_ar":"جَدِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawi A@sotaqaAmuwA EalaY AlT~ariyqapi","text_ar":"لَوِ ا@سْتَقَامُوا عَلَى الطَّرِيقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxii. 16], means, accord. to Fr, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If they had gone on undeviating in the way"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of polytheism:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the right direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqu","text_ar":"طَرَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [It is also used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu TariyqapK","text_ar":"اَهْلُ طَرِيقَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and in like manner the pl., for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu TaraAy^iqa","text_ar":"اَهْلُ طَرَايِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Thus,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aA TaraAy^iqa qidadFA","text_ar":"كُنَّا طَرَايِقَ قِدَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxii. 11], means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were sects differing in our desires."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, O. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qid~apN","text_ar":"قِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tariyqapu Alqawomi","text_ar":"طَرِيقَةُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most excel-lent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA:) and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA rajulN","text_ar":"هٰذَا رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tariyqapu qawomihi","text_ar":"طَرِيقَةُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a man the most excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i Tariyqapu qawomihimo","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ طَرِيقَةُ قَوْمِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqu qawomihimo","text_ar":"طَرَايِقُ قَوْمِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, persons of their people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, * TA:) so says Yaakoob, on the authority of Fr. (S, O, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waya*ohabaA biTariyqatikumu AlmuvolaY","text_ar":"وَيَذْهَبَا بِطَرِيقَتِكُمُ المُثْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xx. 66], means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And that they may take away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your most excellent body of people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, body of people who should be made examples to be followed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and Zj thinks that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTryqtkm","text_ar":"بطريقتكم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aholi Tariyqatikum","text_ar":"بِاَهْلِ طَرِيقَتِكُم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or, accord. to Akh, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your established rule"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"system of religious ordinances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an event: and hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqu Ald~ahori","text_ar":"طَرَايِقُ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The vicissitudes of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  [And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"air"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a song &c.: but this is probably post-classical.] ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A line, streak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a thing: (K, TA:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a crease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrinkle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"often used in this sense:] and [its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqu","text_ar":"طَرَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks, that are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubuk","text_ar":"حُبُك"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a helmet. (TA.) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tariyqap","text_ar":"طَرِيقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"line"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is in the upper part of the back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streak, that extends upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"along"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the back of the ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a rock or the like."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A track"},{"kind":"text","text":"in stony or rugged land &c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narrow strip"},{"kind":"text","text":"of ground or land, and of herbage.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An extended piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strip"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of sand; and likewise of fat; and [likewise of flesh; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oblong piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"of flesh. (TA.) ―         -b6-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqu","text_ar":"طَرَايِقُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment old and worn out"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reduced to strips"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shreds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lh, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu","text_ar":"ذَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqa","text_ar":"طَرَايِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhaA TaraAy^iqu","text_ar":"فِيهَا طَرَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are phrases used, the latter by Dhu-r-Rummeh, in describing a spear-shaft ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaAp","text_ar":"قَنَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":") shrunk by dryness [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what resemble wrinkles, caused by shrinking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iqu","text_ar":"طَرَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last remains of the soft and best portions of pasturage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stages of Heaven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because they lie one above another: (TA:) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~am`waAtu saboEu TaraAy^iqa baEoDuhaA fawoqa baEoDK","text_ar":"السَّمٰوَاتُ سَبْعُ طَرَايِقَ بَعْضُهَا فَوْقَ بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Heavens are seven stages, one above another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Lth, O, TA:) and they have mentioned [likewise] the stages of the earth [as seven in number: and of hell also: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darakN","text_ar":"دَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraqapN","text_ar":"طَرَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b10-  Accord. to Lth, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqapN","text_ar":"طَرِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHoduwrap","text_ar":"اُحْدُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the O and in copies of the K and accord. to the TA, and thus also in the JK,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxoduwdap","text_ar":"اُخْدُودَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (thus accord. to the CK,) [neither of which words have I found in any but this passage, nor do I know any words nearly resembling them except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHoduwr","text_ar":"اُحْدُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxoduwd","text_ar":"اُخْدُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which they may be mistranscriptions, or perhaps dial. vars., the former signifying a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declivity, slope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of descent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furrow, trench,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"border,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sanifap","text_ar":"صَنِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a thing of which one part is stuck upon another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the several portions are stuck one upon another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of colours"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similarly disposed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) ―         -b11-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A web,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing woven, of wool,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats'"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair, a cubit in breadth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in length four cubits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eight cubits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportioned to the size of the tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its length,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is sewed in the place where the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqaAq","text_ar":"شِقَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oblong pieces of cloth that compose the main covering of the tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet, from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisor","text_ar":"كِسْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisor","text_ar":"كِسْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K, TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is app. sewed beneath the middle of the tent-covering, half of its breadth being sewed to one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uq~ap","text_ar":"شُقَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the other half thereof to the other middle"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uq~ap","text_ar":"شُقَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see Burckhardt's “ Bedouins and Wahábys, ” p. 38 of the 8vo ed.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes, it seems, there are three"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iq","text_ar":"طَرَايِق"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in the middle and one towards each side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is added,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in them are the heads of the tentpoles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"these generally consisting of three rows, three in each row,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between which and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TrAy^q","text_ar":"طرايق"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1850},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are pieces of felt, in which are the nozzles"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unuwf","text_ar":"اُنُوف"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tent-poles, in order that these may not rend the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TrAy^q","text_ar":"طرايق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b12-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tent pole; any one of the poles of a tent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"has one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tryqp","text_ar":"طريقة"},{"kind":"text","text":": a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"has two and three and four [and more]: and the part between two poles is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"matonN","text_ar":"مَتْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zbE","text_ar":"زبع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pole of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large tent such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZal~ap","text_ar":"مِظَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b13-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tall palm-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tallest of palm-trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in the dial. of ElYemámeh: (AA, ISk, S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a smooth palmtree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the head of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which may be reached by the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AA, ISk, S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","O","K","Lth","AA","ISk"]},{"entry_id":"n26668","headword_ar":"طِرِّيقَةٌ","root":"Trq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tir~iyqN","text_ar":"طِرِّيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see what next precedes.       -A2-  And also a subst., signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gentleness and submissiveness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"softness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaccidity, and gentleness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"softness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaccidity, and languor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected languor, and weakness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a man; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaroqapN","text_ar":"طَرْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiraAqN","text_ar":"طِرَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHota Tir~iyqatika laEinodaA^owapN","text_ar":"تَحْتَ طِرِّيقَتِكَ لَعِنْدَاْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beneath thy gentleness and submissiveness is occasionally somewhat of hardness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath thy silence is impetuosity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractoriness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath thy silence is deceit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guile."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodaA^owapN","text_ar":"عِنْدَاْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}